advanced_warranty_description:
Two year extended warranty covers hardware failures

Battery covered for one year only

Individual user accidental damage to the device will be covered

Intentional damage, theft and mass-failure related to AoG events/disasters are not covered

Free shipping will be provided both to and from the repair depot

Limitation of coverage per device is up to device resale value

Dedicated Account Manager to ensure your repair needs are fully covered

Customer Central Repair Portal included to seamlessly track and request repairs

Device must either have a protective shell installed, or kept in a locking cart on the school district premises

Self-Maintainer Option - Warranty allows for the ability for the district to be a self-maintainer; i.e., repair devices themselves, or have the warranty provider service the device. In the event the district chooses to service the device, vendor will provide parts as-needed to the district at no additional cost.

Shipping of the replacement part and return shipping of the defective part will be paid for by the vendor. In the event the district opts to service the device, the vendor will provide servicing-time reimbursement in the form of either; A) in-house credit with the vendor or B) payment to the school district; district's choice. Reimbursement or credit is in the amount of $15 per repair.

Mechanical failures in the first year of the warranty do not qualify for the self-maintainer reimbursement, however all other terms apply.
